# Tumeryk Guardrails Client

## Overview

The Tumeryk Guardrails Client is an API client for interacting with Tumeryk Guardrails. It helps users to authenticate, retrieve available policies, set policies, and communicate with the Guard service.

## Example Usage

```python
import tumeryk_guardrails

# Authenticate (replace with valid credentials)
username = "your_username"
password = "your_password"

tumeryk_guardrails.login(username, password)

# Get available policies
policies = tumeryk_guardrails.get_policies()
print("Available Policies:", policies)

# Set a policy if available
tumeryk_guardrails.set_policy("hr_policy")

# Send a guard request
response = tumeryk_guardrails.tumeryk_completions("Example input to guard")
print("Guard Response:", response)
